 verbose command

    (A) FUNCTION
        Verbose command enables/disables to monitor tokens analyzed by
        command interpreter.

    (B) SYNOPSIS

         verbose  [ "on" | "off" ]

    (C) PARAMETERS
       on
       enables to monitor the tokens.

       off
       disables to monitor the tokens.

       (when omitted)
       reports "on" or "off" which tells whether the monitor is
       enabled or not.

    (D) NOTES
        The tokens are reported to claiming-stream.

    (E) SEE ALSO
        2 command interpreter.
